"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The numpy.sinc function computes the normalized sinc function, which is defined as sin(pi*x)/(pi*x) for x != 0 and 1 for x == 0. Therefore, the expected values for sinc_result[1] and sinc_result[2] are not 0.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7c7\\n<assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n---\\n>assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n8c8\\n<assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n>assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], np.sinc(1)), \\\"Results not equal to sinc(1)\\\"\\n9a9\\n>assert np.isclose(sinc_result[2], np.sinc(2)), \\\"Results not equal to sinc(2)\\\"\\n\"\n}"